parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall or not turn off, leading to a risk of fire or accidents.
symptoms: The ignition switch is stuck in one position
the engine won't turn off
smoke or burning smell from the dashboard or engine area
the ignition lock cylinder falls onto the floor
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle won't start
or the starter keeps running even after the key is removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause a fire, leading to a risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from the dashboard or engine area
melted wiring
short circuits
or electrical fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the neutral safety switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the starter keeps running even after the key is removed
or the vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the battery cable can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the battery cable is corroded
or the vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can lead to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt is stuck in place
the seat belt does not move when the door is opened
the seat belt makes a noise but does not work
the cable in the body frame is broken
the seat belt comes out of the holder and falls down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic passive restraint system can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not restrain
the seat belt comes out of track
the mechanism jams
the seat belt does not return to its normal position
the seat belt has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not retract properly, leading to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt is stuck in place
the seat belt makes a noise but does not work
the track gets stuck
the seat belt light stays on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump sending assembly can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel smell inside the vehicle
fuel leaks from the top of the fuel tank
fuel leaks onto the ground
fuel leaks under the back seat
strong fuel odor
fuel gauge malfunctioning
vehicle stalling or not starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the seat belt to stick or malfunction, which can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belt sticks or malfunctions
seat belt will not operate at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Cloudy
yellow
or dim headlights.
